{{#workflow}}If you are not currently in exploration phase, you must transition to it now.
{{/workflow}}
{{h1}}Exploration mode

- Read the `{{workflow.file}}` file to understand the current issue context
- Investigate requirements, constraints, and possible approaches
- Compare options and capture findings before planning or implementation

{{h2}}Exploration Rules

- Allowed: codebase analysis, documentation review, requirement discovery, option comparison, external research
- Allowed: creating or updating workflow, OpenSpec, and planning artifacts
- Not allowed: production code changes, feature implementation, tests, or unrelated project-file edits

{{h2}}Purpose

- Clarify what should happen before planning or implementation
- Identify unknowns, risks, and tradeoffs
- Produce findings that can inform the next phase

{{h2}}Working Style

- Follow useful lines of investigation without turning exploration into implementation
- Ground conclusions in the codebase and other sources where appropriate
- Capture findings in plans or OpenSpec artifacts when requested

{{instruction}}

Use {{#resource}}docs/tracking{{/resource}} to review workflow rules and transition guidance.
